reading assignments







1996 autumn quarter






reading list




  graphics hardware
  
   foley et al., sections 1.5, 4.2 - 4.5
   optional:
    
      i. e. sutherland.  sketchpad: a man-machine graphics
  communication system.   proceedings of the spring joint computer
  conference, 329-346, 1963.
      t. h. myer and i. e. sutherland.  on the design of display
  processors.  communications of the acm  11(6): 410-414, 1968.
    
  
  displaying images
   
   foley et al., sections 4.3.1, 4.4.1, 13 
         (especially 13.1.1, 13.2 (intro), 13.2.1, 13.3.1), 5.4
   optional:
    
     k. sims. artificial evolution for computer graphics.
  computer graphics (siggraph '91) 25(4), 319-328.
    
  
  image morphing
  
   t. beier and s. neely, feature-based image metamorphosis.
  computer graphics (siggraph '92) 26(2), 35-42.
   optional:
    
     a. lerios, c. garfinkle, and m. levoy. feature-based volume
    metamorphosis. computer graphics proceedings, annual
    conference series (siggraph 95), 449-456.
    
  
  texture mapping
   
   foley et al., section 16.3.2, 17.4.3
   neider, davis & woo, chapter 9
   optional:
    
     james f. blinn and martin e. newell.  texture and reflection
    in computer generated images.  communications of the acm 19(10):
    542-547, october 1976.
     paul s. heckbert.  survey of texture mapping.  
    ieee computer graphics and applications 6(11): 56-67, november 1986.
     paul haeberli and mark segal.  texture mapping as a
    fundamental drawing primitive.   proceedings of the fourth
    eurographics workshop on rendering (paris, france), 259-266,
    june 1993. 
    
  
  image compositing
   
   foley et al., section 17.6
   thomas porter and tom duff. compositing digital images. 
       computer graphics (siggraph '84) 18(3), 253-259.
   optional:
    
     neider, davis & woo, chapter 7
    
  
  line drawing
   
   foley et al., sections 3.2, 3.17
   optional:
    
     foley et l., section 14.10
     robert f. sproull.  using program transformations to derive
    line-drawing algorithms.  acm transactions on graphics 1(4):
    259-273, october 1982.
     satish gupta and robert f. sproull.  filtering edges for
    gray-scale displays.   computer graphics 15(3): 1-5, august
    1981.
    
  
  polygon scan conversion
   
   foley et al., sections 3.5, 3.6, 19.2.8
  
  curves
   
   foley et al., sections 11(intro), 11.1.1, 11.2
  
  surfaces
   
   foley et al., section 11.3
  
  hidden surface algorithms
   
   foley et al., chapter 15
   optional:
    
     i. e. sutherland, r. f. sproull, and r. a. schumacker, a 
characterization of ten hidden surface algorithms,  acm computing 
surveys 6(1): 1-55, march 1974.
    
  
  local illumination models
   
   foley et al., sections 16.1, 16.2, 16.5
   optional:
    
     michael oren and shree k. nayar. generalization of lambert's
    reflectance model. computer graphics proceedings, annual
    conference series (siggraph 94), 239-246.
    
  
  ray tracing
   
   foley et al., sections 16.11, 16.12
   optional:
    
     t. whitted. an improved illumination model for shaded
    display.  communications of the acm 23(6), 343-349, 1980.
     j. painter and k. sloan. antialiased ray tracing by adaptive 
    progressive refinement. computer graphics (siggraph 89) 23(3): 
    281-288.
    
  
  rendering tricks
   
   foley et al., sections 16.3, 16.4, 16.6, 16.12.1
   optional:
    
     william t. reeves, david h. salesin, and robert l. cook.
rendering antialiased shadows with depth maps.  computer
graphics (siggraph '87) 21(4): 283-291, july 1987.
     jody duncan shay.  young sherlock holmes: anything but
elementary.  cinefex 26: 36--67, may 1986.
    
  
  global illumination
   
   foley et al., sections 16.7, 16.13
   optional:
    
     c. m. goral, k. e. torrance, d. p. greenberg, et al. modeling
    the interaction of light between diffuse surfaces. computer
    graphics (siggraph '84) 18(3), 213-222.
     b. e. smits, j. r. arvo, and d. h. salesin. an
    importance-driven radiosity algorithm. computer graphics
    (siggraph '92) 26(2), 273-282.
  
  
  wavelets and multiresolution analysis 
   
   optional:
    
    chapters 1-8 in e.j. stollnitz, t.d. derose, d.h. salesin. wavelets
       for computer graphics theory and applications. morgan kaufmann
       publishers, inc.